2017 MONTANA HIGH COUNTRY (BY KEYSTONE) 381TH available in Amelia Court House, Virginia!

This Toy Hauler is ready to take you and your favorite toy on your next adventure and many more!

This Montana is well-equipped inside and out with a great mix of luxury and functionality. The garage is in the rear and loaded by ramp. The garage space can fit a full-size golf cart, motorcycle, or four-wheeler and has a motorcycle wheel chock installed and several tie-down eyes on the floor.

Walking in via the Lippert Solid Steps, you enter a large open kitchen with wood-style flooring, a skylight, a ceiling fan, and a hutch. The kitchen also features loads of cabinets and drawers, a table with extension, four chairs, a residential stainless-steel refrigerator with an ice maker, a three-burner gas stove, a double sink, a microwave, and more!

From the kitchen, step up to the front living room with dual leather recliners, two leather sleeper sofas, a fireplace, a large screen tv, plenty of cabinet space, and two sliders for a huge carpeted living space.

Going toward the rear of the RV, you see the full bath with lots of cabinets, a vanity, a medicine cabinet with a mirror, and a large shower.

Continue down the hall into a large bedroom with a queen bed and full closet space. The bedroom also features accent lighting over the cabinets and a TV.

Outside are two awnings for comfort, four new slide-out cover awnings, an exterior shower, tons of storage, and exterior speakers.

This Montana also has a TST 6 Tire TPMS, a Progressive Industries Power Management System and Surge Protector, and a Furrion Vision 5 backup camera.

Call today to schedule a showing of this great Toy Hauler!

description.raw:
2017 Keystone Springdale Summerland 2820 BH, Stock #232036 -

2017 Keystone RV Summerland Series M-2820BH, all season RV ready to travel anywhere for summer or winter vacations.

The 2017 Springdale Summerland 2820 BH by Keystone is a lightweight trailer that features plenty of accommodations, well-built solid construction, and bunk beds for the kids.

The exterior standards include full exterior pass-thru storage, a power tongue jack, an exterior grill, and exterior speakers.

There is an electronic patio awning with LED lights and pull-out steps.

There are two entry doors. One into the bathroom, the other into the main living area.

Just inside the entry door into the main living area to the right is the master bedroom.

To the left are the kitchen, sofa, and dinette.

The kitchen is equipped with a refrigerator/freezer, a microwave with a hood, a 3-burner stove, an oven, a large kitchen sink with a high pull-out faucet, and drawer and cabinet storage.

Opposite the kitchen area is the single slide that contains the sofa and dinette.

The leatherette sofa is also a jack-knife style bed. It easily opens to create additional sleeping. There is a large window behind it that allows in natural light with overhead storage and lighting.

Next to the sofa is the dinette. The U-shaped dinette provides lots of seating with its U-shape configuration. The dinette table can be dropped to create additional sleeping.

The bunks are located in the rear left side of the Summerland 2820 BH. The bunk beds feature a pull-out ladder easy access to the top bunk. There is also a light in each bunk and separate privacy curtains.

To the right rear of the trailer is where the enclosed bathroom is located.

The bathroom is outfitted with a foot flush toilet, a shower with a skylight, a vanity sink with medicine cabinet, and a ceiling vent with electric fan. As mentioned, there is also a door leading to the outside.

An entertainment center is located at the center of the master bedroom entrance.

The entertainment center has cabinet storage at the top of bottom, a LED TV mounted to a bracket in the center, and an AM/FM/CD/DVD player just below the TV.

The master bedroom is at the front of the trailer.

The queen bed, with an upgraded mattress, has a wardrobe on either side of the bed and also features overhead lighting and a storage shelf.

There are windows on the left and right side of the master bedroom that allows in natural light.

There are shades with curtains on the windows in the trailer.

The exterior sides has the paint protection applied from the dealership at purchase to provide a long-lasting finish.

The electric stabilizing jacks are a very nice addition when setting up your camp.

description.raw:
2019 Keystone Montana 3121RL, Stock #316375 -

2019 Montana by Keystone very well maintained. Self-leveling, full size fridge, fireplace, washer/dryer hook up, ambient lighting.

This is a great example of the 2019 Montana 3121RL. Its single owner has kept it in beautiful condition both inside and out.

Walking around its exterior, the condition shows no scratches, dents, or dings. The tires are in great shape. The roof is well-seated and appears completely seated at its edges.

Entering through the exterior door with a full-screen door, turning right, puts you in the short hallway to the master bedroom. Halfway there is the bathroom with a toilet, full shower, sink, vanity, and mirror.

The bedroom has an upgraded king-sized bed, a full hanging closet behind two sliding doors with mirrors, a small dresser, and a TV...quite a large TV!

Turning left puts you into a great kitchen, dining, and lounging area. The kitchen boasts a full-size, two-door refrigerator with a large pull-out freezer compartment next to a pantry and a small cubby with drawers and a work surface. The island has two sinks and loads of storage space, with the gas stove, full oven, and small wine rack opposite, and to the other side, a nice 4-place dining table with a pullout allowing for two more seats gives the space for a great meal.

The large TV in the lounge is over a very nice rectangular gas fireplace; opposite that are two large reclining lounge chairs. With a three-place couch in between that converts to a twin bed, loads of storage all around, beautiful wood moldings throughout, and tons of room, you'll be set to go.

2013 Keystone Montana 3455sa, Stock #269827 -

2013 Montana 3455SA by Keystone! Sleeps up to 4 w/ 4 Slides! Electric Fireplace, Central Vac, Dual A/C Units, & Much More!

This is a well cared for 2013 Montana fifth wheel. It is a one owner, and has been stored under cover when not in use. The decals are still very colorful.

One of the first things you notice about this unit is the amount of storage space. There are cabinets everywhere!

The living area is in the rear of the unit. The sleeper sofa with a blow up mattress is at the very back. There are two recliners on the left looking at the sofa, and they are facing the television and the fireplace. The television is on a lift and goes into the cabinet when traveling. Above it there is a DVD player and a sound bar.

Going forward you have a dining table and four chairs on your right, and the kitchen island is on the left. The central vacuum system is stored under the sink, and the hose can reach all the way to the bedroom.

The kitchen island gives you lots of food prep space, and contains a double sink. The kitchen itself has a three burner stove with a conventional oven as well as a microwave oven. The refrigerator is a mid size with four doors. A writing table/workstation is next to the pantry.

Going up the stairs you have your controls on the left just before you reach the bathroom. In the bath you have a sink, shower with a skylight and toiletry shelves, a medicine cabinet and of course the toilet. It can be accessed from the hallway, or the bedroom.

The bedroom has a queen size bed with storage underneath. It also has another television, chest of drawers and a huge cedar lined closet. There is another closet with shelving, and it is prepped for a washer and dryer.

Outside you have four slideouts with each one having a topper to keep debris out. It has auto leveling jacks, and it is set up to have an outdoor television if you desire.
